+# Wine Stock Report Generator
+
+A CLI tool that converts a warehouse stock-on-hand CSV into a human-readable Markdown report.
+
+## Installation
+
+No external dependencies required. Requires Python 3.10+.
+
+## Usage
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter CSV_PATH [options]
+```
+
+### Options
+
+| Flag | Default | Description |
+|---|---|---|
+| `--basis {OnHand,Available}` | `Available` | Stock basis for wine totals |
+| `--group-by {variety,vintage,market,pack_size,lot,none}` | `variety` | Group primary wine summary |
+| `--include-dry-goods` / `--no-dry-goods` | include | Dry Goods section toggle |
+| `--low-stock-warnings` / `--no-low-stock-warnings` | on | Low-stock warnings toggle |
+| `--low-stock-threshold N` | `10` | 9LE threshold for low-stock warnings |
+| `--output PATH` | `stock-report.md` | Output Markdown file path |
+| `--no-interactive` | off | Skip all interactive prompts |
+
+### Exit Codes
+
+- `0` — success
+- `1` — data or file error (message printed to stderr)
+- `2` — usage error (argparse-native)
+
+## Interactive Mode
+
+When run without `--no-interactive`, the tool asks 6 clarification questions:
+
+```
+1. Use OnHand or Available stock for wine totals? [Available]:
+2. Include Dry Goods section? [yes]:
+3. Group primary wine summary by variety, vintage, market, pack_size, lot, or none? [variety]:
+4. Include low-stock warnings? [yes]:
+5. Low-stock threshold in 9LE? [10]:
+6. Output filename? [stock-report.md]:
+```
+
+Press Enter to accept the default for any question. EOF (Ctrl-D) accepts defaults for the current and all remaining questions.
+
+## Example
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv --no-interactive --output report.md
+```
+
+## Running Tests
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest discover -s tests
+```
+
+## Report Structure
+
+The generated Markdown report includes:
+
+1. **Header** — generated date, source file, warehouse(s), stock basis
+2. **Executive Summary** — row counts, totals, lowest stock item, warning count
+3. **Stock by [Group]** — grouped summary table (when `group_by != none`)
+4. **Detailed Finished Goods** — full row-level table with 9LE values
+5. **Low Stock Warnings** — items below the 9LE threshold (when enabled)
+6. **Dry Goods Summary** — dry goods rows (when included)
+7. **Data Warnings** — validation and parse warnings
+
+## 9LE Calculation
+
+9LE (9-litre equivalent) = `cases × pack_size × bottle_size_ml / 1000 / 9`
+
+All arithmetic uses `decimal.Decimal` to avoid floating-point drift.
